Another lone accident has claimed the life of one person while six others in the car were injured at various degrees. According to an accident report from the Ganjuwa LGA Station of the Federal Roads Safety Corps (FRSC) released by the State Command Headquarters on Sunday, the accident occurred at 0905hrs on Sunday and was reported at 0910hrs while FRSC personnel arrived at the scene at 0920hrs 10mins after. The lone accident occurred at Kafin Kawu Village in Ganjuwa LGA on the Bauchi-Kano highway involving a private Honda Civic UK saloon car with registration number, CX904RBC. According to the report by DRC KM CHADI, STO of the FRSC in GANJUWA LGA the car was driven by one GHALI Idris while the possible cause of the accident was speed limit violation (SPV). The number of the occupants of the car was seven out of which six male adults were injured while one male adult was killed. All the victims and corpses were taken to Kafin Madaki General Hospital by Ganjuwa LGA Division of NPF for treatment and confirmation. YOU SHOULD NOT MISS THESE FROM NIGERIAN TRIBUNE ‘Officials initially offered to help but when the number of able-bodied citizens at the centre increased, they left us unattended to’
